mance e acessibilidade específicas para PO-UI + Angular"],[1792,"**Root cause (confirmed by PO-UI source):**\n`PoPageContentComponent` sets `contentOpacity = 0` on creation and calls\n`recalculateHeaderSize()` in `ngAfterViewInit`, which uses `setTimeout` to set\n`contentOpacity = 1`. In **OnPush** components without an async data load (e.g., using\nsynchronous demo data), the component is already \"clean\" when that `setTimeout` fires —\nAngular skips the entire subtree during CD and `contentOpacity = 1` is never reflected\nin the DOM. Components that make HTTP requests are \"accidentally\" safe because the HTTP\nresponse triggers a `markForCheck()` after the `setTimeout` has already run."],[1856,"**Root cause (verified against PO-UI source):**"],[1872,"**Root cause (verified against PO-UI source):**"],[1834,"**Root cause:** `p-selected-rows` is not an output of `po-table`. The correct outputs for\nrow selection are individual-row events, not a batch-selection array."],[1797,"**Root cause:** `po-input` renders a wrapper that includes an invisible 8px space below\nthe visible input field, reserved for validation error messages. `flex-end` aligns to the\nbottom of this wrapper (including the invisible 8px), not to the bottom of the visible field."],[1853,"**Root cause:** `PoTableDetail.columns` uses the internal type `PoTableDetailColumn`, which is a subset of `PoTableColumn` and does **not** include `width`. The `width` property is only valid on master columns (`PoTableColumn[]`), not on detail columns."],[1801,"**Root cause:** po-table adds an internal selectable-column (`po-table-column-selectable`)\nof **56px** that is NOT represented in `PoTableColumn[]`. This hidden 56px is added on\ntop of the sum of all `p-width` values, pushing the table wider than its container."],[1839,"**Root cause:** po-table adds the row to its internal `selectedRows` array **before**\ndispatching the `(p-selected)` event. Any synchronous `$selected: false` change on the\nitems signal i